lender.name: Christoph
lender.loan_because:
When thinking about how to best help others within the means possible for me, I often end up at development help in the form of donations.
However while this seems to make sense when trying to support environmental groups or groups striving to protect animal rights, it seems to lack when concerning other, less privileged people.
Development help too often causes temporary improvement, which does not continue once the money dries up. Through loans I hope that people are supported in taking responsibility and that it helps make everyone more independent, creating a lasting change in their local community.
Since it takes some action and initiative to arrive at Kiva and request loans, it seems just right to help.
